<div class="ten columns offset-by-one intro">
  <p> "We are all different, which is great because we are all unique. Without diversity life would be very boring." -Catherine Pulsifer</p>
</div>

    <div class="ten columns offset-by-one contentBox">
      <div class="six columns twitterResults">
        <%= form_tag("/reroute", method: "post") do %>
          <label for="twitter_handle">TWITTER HANDLE:</label>
          
          <div class="ui labeled input">
            <div class="ui label">
              @
            </div>
            <input id="twitterHandle" type="text" name="twitter_handle" placeholder="TwitterHandle">
          </div>

          <button id="getResults" class="button-primary">Your Results</button>
        <% end %>
          
          <div class="error">
            <%= flash[:message] %>
          </div>

          <div id="searchHelp" class="searchHelp">Who should I search for?</div>

          <div class="searchHelp__title">YOURSELF</div>
          <div class="searchHelp__message">How diverse is your feed? Are you exposed primarily to viewpoints similar to yours?</div>

          <div class="searchHelp__title">ELECTED OFFICALS</div>
          <div class="searchHelp__message">Are your representatives paying attention to the myriad of voices that comprise their constituency?</div>

          <div class="searchHelp__title">YOUR FAVORITE JOURNALIST</div>
          <div class="searchHelp__message">Are they seeking information from a wide variety of people?</div>

      </div>

      <div class="six columns twitterData">

        <% if session[:screen_name] == nil %>
          <label for="getStarted">ADD YOUR INFO:</label>

          <a href="/auth/twitter"><button class="button-primary" name="getStarted">Get Started</button></a>
        <% else %>
            <label for="editInfo">@<%= session[:screen_name].upcase %></label>
            <a href="/users/<%= session[:screen_name] %>/edit"><button class="button" name="editInfo">EDIT YOUR INFO</button></a>
        <% end %>

          <div id="dataHelp" class="dataHelp">What happens to my data?</div>

          <div class="dataHelp__title">MORE ACCURATE DATA</div>
          <div class="dataHelp__message">The greater percentage of twitter users who participate, the more complete and meaningful the data.</div>

          <div class="dataHelp__title">ITâ€™S KEPT ANONYMOUSS</div>
          <div class="dataHelp__message">We keep any identifying information hidden in results; we're working to encrypt information for added security.</div>

          <div class="dataHelp__title">ONLY SHARE WHAT YOU WANT</div>
          <div class="dataHelp__message">Seriously, no pressure. Not comfortable answering a question? Just leave it blank.</div>

      </div>
    </div>
